Some people with disabilities may have a higher risk of #COVID19 illness. Talk to your patients about health conditions that might put them at higher risk for COVID-19 and the importance of getting a COVID-19 vaccine.
https://t.co/tECS1kySF4 https://t.co/bwQbxmGPz8

HCPs: #COVID19 vaccinations are free for everyone. Vaccination providers can’t charge patients any fee, but they can seek appropriate reimbursement from the recipient’s plan or program for a vaccine administration fee. Learn more: https://t.co/VflxH9JKbe https://t.co/lKa8Ypge9O

You should get a #COVID19 vaccine even if you’ve already had COVID-19.
As of March 22, more than 82.7 million people in the United States had received at least one dose of COVID-19 vaccine. Of those, more than 44.9 million are fully vaccinated. 
More data: https://t.co/FHGplToHFM https://t.co/XKtzmSY3ib
RT @CDCgov: Subscribe to get CDC’s COVID Data Tracker Weekly Review sent to your inbox every Friday: https://t.co/m5w5IKMJIv.

Educators now have wider access to #COVID19 vaccines. CDC’s new toolkit for school settings and childcare programs provides vaccine information to help educational leaders communicate with staff about the benefits of vaccination. Learn more: https://t.co/EFpx8mQ0wv https://t.co/TgsmOgxrz1
Stay up to date with the facts about #COVID19 vaccines. Visit https://t.co/MINLCLmQrC to learn more. #SleeveUpForSchools https://t.co/wnJVq18Kbt

#COVID19 vaccines are under the most intense safety monitoring in U.S. history. 

Nearly 74 million people in the U.S. have already received COVID-19 vaccines as of March 17. Get vaccinated when a COVID-19 vaccine is available to you. 

Learn more: https://t.co/VMKo4JPjFI https://t.co/kVaqgloRCt

We are sticking with current recommendations about the timing and strength of #COVID19 vaccines, which were proven to be protective in clinical trials. We’ll continue to follow the data and the science. 

Thank you @HelenBranswell for asking the tough questions. https://t.co/5NxroxwHKv

School and childcare staff can #SleeveUp at state and local #COVID19 vaccination sites and at more than 9,000 pharmacies nationwide. 

Find participating pharmacies in your state: https://t.co/e39JQThhoT 
#SleeveUpforSchools
#SleeveUpforChildcare https://t.co/NrpusYStdh

In the coming weeks & months, #COVID19 vaccine supply will increase.
As of March 15, more than 71 million people in the United States had received at least one dose of COVID-19 vaccine. Of those, more than 38 million are fully vaccinated. 
See more data: https://t.co/FHGplToHFM https://t.co/JD64gdDMsn

All states must make teachers, school staff, & childcare workers eligible for #COVID19 shots. Pharmacies in CDC’s Federal Retail Pharmacy Program are now giving priority to school & childcare staff for COVID-19 shots during March. Learn more:  https://t.co/e39JQSZGxl https://t.co/dnpdcvoUvV

Vaccination Providers: Encourage people to sign up for v-safe after #COVID19 vaccination. V-safe is now available in English, Spanish, Vietnamese, Korean, and simplified Chinese. Your recommendation matters. https://t.co/PZb1Xsr8sG https://t.co/enWfvR4arD

#HCPs: CDC issued interim recommendations for the use of the Janssen #COVID19 vaccine (Johnson & Johnson) in the U.S. for people 18 and older. Read these considerations and those for other COVID-19 vaccines: https://t.co/fEXOVu1QyW https://t.co/L2nyK2zkUr

Johnson & Johnson’s Janssen #COVID19 vaccine is the third vaccine authorized for use in the United States. This one-dose vaccine is recommended for people 18 and older.

Learn more about the J&J/Janssen vaccine: https://t.co/zZ0kI19gHe https://t.co/mLYt02bQV6
On today's COCA call at 2pm ET, learn effective strategies for responding to #COVID19 vaccine safety and efficacy questions you may hear. https://t.co/WjL6ujRhIw

#COVID19 vaccines are safe and effective. 
As of March 8, over 60 million people in the US had received at least one dose of COVID-19 vaccine. Of those, more than 31 million had received two doses. 
See more data: https://t.co/FHGplTGixk https://t.co/achMsVb0rM

#HCPs: Your patients trust you as a source of #COVID19 vaccine information. Your strong recommendation to get the vaccine is important. These tips can help you have effective conversations with your patients: https://t.co/MeYcRHJ8J2 https://t.co/gExx4FdSwH

No safety concerns have been found during early #COVID19 vaccine safety monitoring, except rare reports of anaphylaxis. CDC has provided recommendations to vaccination providers on preparing for the possibility. Get a vaccine when it’s available to you. https://t.co/wKcKrljgiV https://t.co/s3TQBPkQa1

#LongTermCare facility healthcare providers: Your decision to get a #COVID19 vaccine can protect more than just your own health. It can also help protect your patients, colleagues, family, and community. Get vaccinated with confidence. Learn more: https://t.co/f2wYKadBnX https://t.co/ZYGmVlfAjx

Despite some technical issues, it was great to talk with JAMA’s Dr. Howard Bauchner about #COVID19 vaccines.
@JAMA_current https://t.co/zOdDIU2lXe

Stopping the pandemic requires using all the tools we have, including all authorized and recommended #COVID19 vaccines. Remember, continue to wear a mask, stay 6 feet apart, avoid crowds and poorly ventilated spaces, and wash your hands. Get vaccinated when it’s available to you. https://t.co/2ukCK5qMLo

#COVID19 vaccines are an important tool to stop the pandemic. 
As of March 1, over 50 million people had received their first dose of COVID-19 vaccine. Of those, more than 25 million people had received both doses & are fully vaccinated. 
See more data: https://t.co/FHGplToHFM https://t.co/uBPwS4Wf3F

Today, the Advisory Committee on Immunization Practices continues 2-day meeting. Having recommended J&J/Janssen #COVID19 vaccine on Sunday, #ACIP will address clinical considerations and hear vaccine safety update. Webcast starts at 11am ET: 
https://t.co/SQeQbRju3n

Earlier today Advisory Committee on Immunization Practices recommended third authorized #COVID19 vaccine for use in US & @CDCgov adopted the recommendation. CDC recommends vaccines be offered first to people #ACIP identified as a priority population. See: https://t.co/WlGmsjv1al https://t.co/McAH5l2FWo
